  {
    "id": 1,
    "title": {
      "English": "Greetings",
      "Oshikwanyama": "Wa lele po?"
    },
    "description": "Greet first before asking or saying anything. Always take time and shake hands when greeting. Greet elders first. Words like Meme (mother), Tate (father), and especially Meekulu (grandmother) and Tatekulu (grandfather) show respect and are just as important as the greeting itself.\n\nLiterally, if someone says Wa lele po, they are asking if you laid down last night. Wa uhala po asks if you spent the afternoon, and wa tokelwa po asks if the sky became white for you at dusk.",
